symbols.name: dataPublisher
symbols.brief: The dataPublisher class is a virtual class used by other publishers to distribute data online.

children.name: DreamHostPublisher
children.brief: The DreamHostPublisher subclass of dataPublisher is for publishing data to the Stroud Center's now-deprecated DreamHost based live sensor data system.

children.name: EnviroDIYPublisher
children.brief: The EnviroDIYPublisher subclass of dataPublisher for publishing data to the Monitor My Watershed/EnviroDIY data portal at http://data.enviroDIY.org.

children.name: ThingSpeakPublisher
children.brief: The ThingSpeakPublisher subclass of dataPublisher for publishing data to ThingSpeak using the MQTT protocol.

children.name: UbidotsPublisher
children.brief: The UbidotsPublisher subclass of dataPublisher for publishing data to the Ubidots data portal at https://ubidots.com.

symbols.name: extendedWatchDogAVR
symbols.brief: The extendedWatchDogAVR class uses the pre-reset interrupt to of the built in AVR watchdog to extend the allowable time between resets of the watchdog's clock up to multiple minute timescales.

symbols.name: extendedWatchDogSAMD
symbols.brief: The extendedWatchDogSAMD class uses the early warning interrupt to of the built in SAMD watchdog to extend the allowable time between resets of the watchdog's clock up to multiple minute timescales.

symbols.name: Logger
symbols.brief: The "Logger" Class handles low power sleep for the main processor, interfacing with the real-time clock and modem, writing to the SD card, and passing data on to the data publishers.

symbols.name: loggerModem
symbols.brief: The loggerModem class provides an internet connection for the logger and supplies an Arduino Client instance to use to publish data.
